# Latent Space Labs — ICP local development environment
#
# Copy to `.env` (git-ignored) and fill in with your own credentials.
# See docs/decisions/0017-icp-credentials-and-secrets-management.md
# for scope expectations, rotation cadence, and the rule that skills
# load these via the typed ICP config module, never via process.env.
#
# Placeholders here MUST NOT look like real tokens. Replace them in
# your local `.env` only; do not commit real values to any file.

# --- Perplexity / MCP bridge ------------------------------------------
# Bearer token issued by the Perplexity agent proxy (`agp_*`). Loaded by
# `.mcp.json` at harness start via ${AUTH_TOKEN} interpolation.
# Scope: whatever the proxy issues; do not reuse as a generic API key.
AUTH_TOKEN=agp_CHANGEME

# --- Linear -----------------------------------------------------------
# Personal API key (`lin_api_*`).
# Scope: read + write issues, comments, relations, labels, states in the
# LAT team. NO admin / billing / integration-install / webhook scope.
# Consumed by the Linear adapter under LAT-60 once the typed loader lands.
LINEAR_API_KEY=lin_api_CHANGEME

# --- GitHub -----------------------------------------------------------
# Fine-grained PAT (`ghp_*` or `github_pat_*`) scoped to the
# BenjaminDElliott/latentspacelabs repository only.
# Permissions: contents:read/write, pull-requests:read/write,
# issues:read/write. NO workflow-edit, admin, or org-level scope.
# Interactive operators may instead rely on `gh auth login` and leave
# this empty; the adapter will pick up `gh`'s credential when present.
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_CHANGEME
